open ubuntu terminal
type the following command to set up the boost library:
0/ sudo apt install google-perftools libgoogle-perftools-dev libboost-dev (if error shows, execute 'sudo apt-get update' first)

For jumna++ install:
type the following commands:
1/ wget http://lotus.kuee.kyoto-u.ac.jp/nl-resource/jumanpp/jumanpp-1.02.tar.xz
2/ tar xJvf jumanpp-1.02.tar.xz
3/ cd jumanpp-1.02
4/ ./configure
5/ make
6/ sudo make install

For KNP install:
type the following commands:
1/ wget -O knp-4.20.tar.bz2 https://nlp.ist.i.kyoto-u.ac.jp/DLcounter/lime.cgi?down=https://nlp.ist.i.kyoto-u.ac.jp/nl-resource/knp/knp-4.20.tar.bz2&name=knp-4.20.tar.bz2
2/ tar jxvf knp-4.20.tar.bz2
3/ cd knp-4.20
4/ ./configure
5/ make
6/ sudo make install

To install pyknp package to use juman and knp:
type pip install pyknp
